The paper describes a system for organizing scientific literature into a graph, which involves natural language processing tasks such as entity extraction and linking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses challenges in constructing the graph, which could be related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the constructed graph to enable semantic features, which could be relevant to Databases (cs.DB).
